    <question>
        <prompt>How did the end of Reconstruction affect land ownership?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Reversed many freedmen's land gains</option>
            <option letter="b">Increased black land ownership</option>
            <option letter="c">Distributed more federal land</option>
            <option letter="d">Created new homestead programs</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The end of Reconstruction led to the reversal of many freedmen's land gains as former Confederate owners reclaimed property and new restrictions limited land acquisition.</explanation>
    </question>
